            "guideHtml": "\n                <div style=\"color: var(--text-main); line-height: 1.8; font-size: 13px;\">\n                    <h2 style=\"color: var(--twitch-purple); font-size: 18px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-color); padding-bottom: 8px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">◆ Help</h2>\n                    \n                    <section style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\n                        <h3 style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #bf94ff; margin-bottom: 12px;\">1. Setup Twitch Integration</h3>\n                        <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 15px;\">\n                            <li><strong>Twitch Token Generator:</strong> Choose Custom Scope Token, select the required scopes, and generate an ACCESS TOKEN.</li>\n                            <li><strong>Access Token:</strong> Paste the generated ACCESS TOKEN into Settings and save it. The Client ID and channel ID are detected automatically.</li>\n                            <li><strong>Renewal:</strong> If Apply or Sync shows an auth error, generate a new Access Token with the same steps and save it again.</li>\n                        </ul>\n                        <div style=\"background: rgba(255, 74, 74, 0.1); border-left: 4px solid #ff4a4a; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n                            <strong style=\"color: #ff4a4a;\">⚠️ Security Warning (!)</strong><br>\n                            Your Access Token represents your actual streaming permissions. Do not share it with third parties or show it on stream. If leaked, revoke the connection in Twitch and generate a new token.\n                        </div>\n                    </section>\n\n                    <section style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\n                        <h3 style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #bf94ff; margin-bottom: 12px;\">2. About \"Save\" and \"Apply\"</h3>\n                        <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px; color: var(--text-muted);\">\n                            <li><strong>Save / Auto-Save:</strong> Records content in your browser (cache). Kept even if you close the tool.</li>\n                            <li><strong>Apply (PUSH):</strong> Sends your edits to actual Twitch stream info, directly overwriting Title and Category.</li>\n                            <li><strong>Sync:</strong> Loads the current actual Twitch stream info into this tool.</li>\n                        </ul>\n                        <p style=\"font-size: 11px; color: #adadb8; background: #252529; padding: 8px; border-radius: 6px;\">* Note: Due to current Twitch API specs, Tags and Notifications cannot be directly overwritten from the tool. Please use them as a \"Memo\" feature here.</p>\n                    </section>\n\n                    <section style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\n                        <h3 style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #bf94ff; margin-bottom: 12px;\">3. Backup (!)</h3>\n                        <ul style=\"padding-left: 20px; color: var(--text-muted);\">\n                            <li>To prepare for browser cache deletion, regularly save your data as text from the \"Backup\" tab.</li>\n                            <li>Since direct file saving isn't possible from an OBS dock, please copy & paste to a notepad, etc.</li>\n                            <li>When changing PCs or restoring data, load the saved text.</li>\n                            <li>If you have a lot of data, copying to the clipboard might fail, so please organize/delete data regularly.</li>\n                        </ul>\n                    </section>\n\n                    <section style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\n                        <a href=\"https://note.com/konpeito_fox/n/na3b5b6d69748\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: block; background: #252529; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #fff; text-decoration: none; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center; font-weight: bold;\">📖 Open Detailed Manual (note)</a>\n                    </section>\n\n                    <div style=\"font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-muted); border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 15px;\">\n                        <strong>[Disclaimer]</strong><br>\n                        This is a personal tool. While checked thoroughly, there's always a non-zero chance of unexpected bugs causing data loss. To protect your data, use at your own risk and back up frequently. Contact via DM/X reply for questions.\n                    </div>\n                </div>",
